/*The first version of this program 'PrepareCostReporting' is used to be part of the QRAP-Xml-reporting. This causes a huge performance penalty on the single instance XQP-queue processor. In time Some features of this data collection where already duplicated and produced in the calculatePerformanceData Main funtion. This new program will produce performancecalculationamounts 801--899) The performanceCalculationAmounts collected in the range 201-207) for the End of Period Year (801-819) End of Year -1 (821-839) and end of year -2 (841-859) NB categories 801-807 are duplicates of 201-207 and should equal the corresponding 8## amounts on total level (asset-class =0 (no instrument or account) distinction. The Y-1 and Y-2 categories are produced with the same logic only difference is the startDate
Possibly duplicated CalcCategories during the design of this function should be removed next release/

Text.val: Persisted Calculation Amounts Y-2 the year before previous year)

SQL_STMT_U.val: select 'P', sum(b.value) from pc_portfolio_base b where b.pere_id = ~1 and b.calc_date = to_date(~2, 'YYYY-MM-DD') union select 'A', sum(b.value) from pc_account_base b where b.pere_id = ~1 and b.calc_date = to_date(~2, 'YYYY-MM-DD') union select 'I', sum(a.amount*a.factor) from pc_portfolio_amount a inner join pc_portfolio_base b on b.id=a.pcpb_id and b.calc_date = to_date(~2, 'YYYY-MM-DD') where b.pere_id = ~1 and a.pcca_id = ~3

select sum(amount) amount, sum(a.amount*(to_date( ~3 , 'YYYY-MM-DD')-b.transaction_date+1)/(to_date( ~3 , 'YYYY-MM-DD')-to_date( ~2 , 'YYYY-MM-DD')+1)) weigthed_amount from pc_transaction_amount a inner join pc_transaction_base b on b.id = a.pctb_id inner join pc_category c on c.id = a.pcca_id where b.pere_id = ~1 and c.code = 204 and b.transaction_date between to_date(~2 , 'YYYY-MM-DD') and to_date( ~3 , 'YYYY-MM-DD')
